      "span_text": "Therefore, the absorption of serum proteins on MWCNTs would not be necessary for cell adhesion, rather, one of the reasons suggested was that steric nanostructure of the MWCNT-coated surface, which looks like a sea-anemone, might be effective in entrapping the cell while the cells pass through the vertical wall of the sponge pore.  .",
